I solved the halting problem, it doesn't exist. Just check every n + 1
clock cycles whether the previous savestate (a term from speedrunning)
matches the current savestate exactly, byte for byte. You can discard
the previous previous savestate.

n can be a arbitrary precision integer. You add 1 to n every time you
check. Also, my algorithm detects all infinite loops, but some infinite
loops may be whitelisted like the OS kernel.

Now where's my million dollars for proving P=NP...

The Halting Problem Solution Idea Subproject is dedicated to the Public
Domain, however, once I add some code, that code will be licensed under
The VitaSet License, but the idea will remain dedicated to the Public
Domain.
